## Scripts

All scripts are in `{{project_dir}}/scripts/` and load configuration from `{{project_dir}}/config/`.

### company_classifier.py

Classify a company as "startup" or "large" for outreach tone adjustment.

```bash
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/company_classifier.py "Stripe"
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/company_classifier.py "Acme Corp" --add startup
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/company_classifier.py "Google" --json
```

### save_job.py

Save a job posting as structured JSON for tracking and linking to outreach.

```bash
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/save_job.py save --company "Stripe" --role "Product Manager" --url "https://..." --location "San Francisco" --salary "180k-220k" --source linkedin --status applied
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/save_job.py list
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/save_job.py link-outreach --job-id "2026-04-07-stripe-product-manager" --outreach-id "john-doe-stripe"
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/save_job.py link-cover-letter --job-id "2026-04-07-stripe-product-manager" --path "outputs/cover-letters/stripe-pm.md"
```

### update_outreach.py

Log outreach, update outcomes, and view stats.

```bash
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/update_outreach.py log --name "John" --company "Stripe" --role recruiter --type connection-request --message "Hi John, ..." --job-id "2026-04-07-stripe-product-manager"
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/update_outreach.py update --name "John" --company "Stripe" --status accepted
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/update_outreach.py update --name "John" --company "Stripe" --status replied --date 2026-04-10
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/update_outreach.py stats
```

### smart_template.py

Generate LinkedIn outreach messages (connection requests, InMails, LinkedIn messages) based on company size and recipient role. Includes A/B test variants.

```bash
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/smart_template.py --name "Sarah" --company "Plaid" --job-title "Product Manager" --role recruiter --type connection-request
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/smart_template.py --name "Mike" --company "Google" --job-title "Senior PM" --role hiring-manager --type inmail
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/smart_template.py --name "Lisa" --company "Notion" --job-title "PM" --role peer --type linkedin-message
```

