### generate_pdf.py

Generate professional PDFs from markdown cover letters or resumes.

```bash
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/generate_pdf.py --type cover-letter --input outputs/cover-letters/stripe-pm.md --company Stripe
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/generate_pdf.py --type resume --input path/to/resume.md
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/generate_pdf.py --type cover-letter --input outputs/cover-letters/stripe-pm.md --output ~/Downloads/custom-name.pdf
```

### score_messages.py

Analyze outreach history to find best-performing message patterns, broken down by message type, company size, and recipient role.

```bash
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/score_messages.py
```

### fetch_jobs.py

Fetch jobs via JSearch (RapidAPI). Searches across LinkedIn, Indeed, Glassdoor, and ZipRecruiter. Deduplicates results and maintains a master job repository.

```bash
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/fetch_jobs.py
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/fetch_jobs.py --keywords "Product Manager" "AI PM"
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/fetch_jobs.py --locations "New York" "Remote"
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/fetch_jobs.py --keywords "Data Analyst" --max-jobs 50
```

**Environment variables required:**
- `RAPIDAPI_KEY` for JSearch (free: 200 req/month)

### dashboard.py / local_server.py / generate_data_js.py

Local HTML dashboard infrastructure. `dashboard.py` regenerates `dashboard/data.js` (the embedded data fallback), starts the local server at `http://localhost:8777`, and auto-opens the browser. The server reads and writes `data/tracking.json` via `/api/tracking*` endpoints. Use `dashboard.py` as the daily command:

```bash
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/dashboard.py               # regen + serve + open browser
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/dashboard.py --no-browser  # headless / SSH
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/dashboard.py --port 9000   # custom port
```

### match_connections.py

Match `data/connections.csv` against `data/jobs/all-jobs.json` and write `data/connection-matches.json`. Called automatically at the end of `fetch_jobs.py`; can also be run manually to refresh matches without re-fetching.

```bash
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/match_connections.py
```

### migrate_outreach_to_tracking.py

One-shot migration from the legacy `data/outreach-history.json` format to the unified `data/tracking.json` schema. Idempotent — safe to re-run.

```bash
cd {{project_dir}} && python3 scripts/migrate_outreach_to_tracking.py
```

